<subSubSection id="C34A6528FFE7FFC6A5CDFA531A8DF961" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BEF36A3FFE7FFC6A5CDFA531FD1FA65" blockId="23.[136,494,1418,1445]" box="[136,494,1418,1445]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
<heading id="D0A781CFFFE7FFC6A5CDFA531FD1FA65" box="[136,494,1418,1445]" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" reason="4">
8. 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D20FFE7FFC6A5E1FA521FD5FA65" authority="Linnaeus (1753: 626)" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityPageNumber="626" authorityYear="1753" box="[164,490,1418,1445]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Petrea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFE7FFC6A5E1FA521ED0FA65" bold="true" box="[164,239,1419,1445]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Petrea</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFE7FFC6A5B3FA531FD5FA65" author="Linnaeus, C. von" box="[246,490,1418,1445]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" pagination="1 - 1200" refId="ref35181" refString="Linnaeus, C. von (1753) Species Plantarum. L. Salvius, Stockholm, pp. 1 - 1200." type="book chapter" year="1753">Linnaeus (1753: 626)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEF36A3FFE7FFC6A5CDFA0B1A8DF961" blockId="23.[136,1452,1490,1913]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Lianas, monoecious, branches without prickles, not aromatic. Leaves petiolate, glands near to the petiole absent. Inflorescences axillary, simple, racemes spiciform; rachis elongated; bracts membranaceous, lilac; bracteoles absent. Flowers pedicellate; calyx tubular, petaloid, longer than the corolla, membranaceous, purple or lilac, 5-lobed, lobes obtuse, persistent, accrescent in fruit; corolla zygomorphic, 5-lobed; stamens 4, included, didynamous, superior pair without connective appendages, thecae introrse; ovary 1-carpelate, 2-loculate, ovules 1 per locule, stigma obliques. Fruit drupe, with 2 pyrenes, brown, external surface striate in the base, rugose toward the apex.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34A6528FFE7FFC6A5F8F9721DE8F8B8" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="8BEF36A3FFE7FFC6A5F8F9721DE8F8B8" blockId="23.[136,1452,1490,1913]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
<taxonomicName id="4C504D20FFE7FFC6A5F8F9721F38F904" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[189,263,1707,1732]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Petrea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFE7FFC6A5F8F9721F38F904" box="[189,263,1707,1732]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Petrea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is part of the tribe 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D20FFE7FFC6A491F9721D3CF904" authority="(Marx et al. 2010)" baseAuthorityName="Marx" baseAuthorityYear="2010" box="[468,771,1706,1733]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="tribe" tribe="Petreeae">
Petreeae (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFE7FFC6A705F9731CC4F904" author="Marx, H. &amp; O'Leary, N. &amp; Yuan, Y. &amp; Lu-Irving, P. &amp; Tank, D. &amp; Mulgura, M. E. &amp; Olmstead, R." box="[576,763,1706,1732]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" pagination="1647 - 1663" refId="ref35509" refString="Marx, H., O'Leary, N., Yuan, Y., Lu-Irving, P., Tank, D., Mulgura, M. E. &amp; Olmstead, R. (2010) A molecular phylogeny and classification of Verbenaceae. American Journal of Botany 97: 1647 - 1663. https: // doi. org / 10.3732 / ajb. 1000144" type="journal article" year="2010">
Marx 
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFE7FFC6A7C0F9721C83F904" box="[645,700,1706,1732]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">et al.</emphasis>
2010
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and presents 12 species distributed from the South of Mexico to 
<collectingCountry id="F3477633FFE7FFC6A5E0F9171F28F928" box="[165,279,1742,1768]" name="Argentina" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Argentina</collectingCountry>
, with most of the richness concentrated in the Amazon Forest (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFE7FFC6A6A2F9171A4CF928" author="Rueda, R. M." box="[999,1139,1742,1768]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" pagination="610 - 652" refId="ref37895" refString="Rueda, R. M. (1994) Systematics and evolution of the genus Petrea (Verbenaceae). Annals of the Missouri Botanical Garden 81: 610 - 652. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 2399914" type="journal article" year="1994">Rueda 1994</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFE7FFC6A1C5F9161B7DF928" author="Marx, H. &amp; O'Leary, N. &amp; Yuan, Y. &amp; Lu-Irving, P. &amp; Tank, D. &amp; Mulgura, M. E. &amp; Olmstead, R." box="[1152,1346,1742,1769]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" pagination="1647 - 1663" refId="ref35509" refString="Marx, H., O'Leary, N., Yuan, Y., Lu-Irving, P., Tank, D., Mulgura, M. E. &amp; Olmstead, R. (2010) A molecular phylogeny and classification of Verbenaceae. American Journal of Botany 97: 1647 - 1663. https: // doi. org / 10.3732 / ajb. 1000144" type="journal article" year="2010">
Marx 
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFE7FFC6A180F9161AC0F928" box="[1221,1279,1742,1768]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">et al.</emphasis>
2010
</bibRefCitation>
, Cardoso 
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFE7FFC6A5CDF92A1F19F8CC" box="[136,294,1778,1804]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">et al. in press</emphasis>
.). The genus is characterized by the presence of a calyx longer than the corolla, protecting it in the pre-formation, as well as the ovary after the senescence of the corolla, also attracting pollinators and aiding the fruit dispersal (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFE7FFC6A5BEF8E31FB7F894" author="Rueda, R. M." box="[251,392,1850,1876]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" pagination="610 - 652" refId="ref37895" refString="Rueda, R. M. (1994) Systematics and evolution of the genus Petrea (Verbenaceae). Annals of the Missouri Botanical Garden 81: 610 - 652. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 2399914" type="journal article" year="1994">Rueda 1994</bibRefCitation>
). Eight species occur in 
<collectingCountry id="F3477633FFE7FFC6A7DBF8E31CDAF894" box="[670,741,1850,1876]" name="Brazil" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, of which three are endemic, and two are found in the Atlantic Forest (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFE7FFC6A598F8871C27F8B8" author="Cardoso, P. H. &amp; Salimena, F. R. G." box="[221,536,1886,1912]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" refId="ref33390" refString="Cardoso, P. H. &amp; Salimena, F. R. G. (2020 a) Petrea in Flora do Brasil 2020 under construction. Jardim Botanico do Rio de Janeiro. Available from: http: // floradobrasil. jbrj. gov. br / reflora / floradobrasil / FB 15183 (accessed 4 January 2021)" type="url" year="2020">Cardoso &amp; Salimena 2020a</bibRefCitation>
). There is one species in 
<collectingRegion id="4994F841FFE7FFC6A675F8871DECF8B8" box="[816,979,1886,1912]" country="Brazil" name="Espirito Santo" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Espírito Santo</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
